# MindMosaic Engineering Rules

## Project

MindMosaic is a premium educational practice portal for Grade 3 and
Grade 5 NAPLAN-style and ICAS-style questions.

## Non-negotiable rules

- Never copy official NAPLAN, ICAS, textbook, website or commercial questions.
- Generate only original educational content.
- Preserve the governed question-factory lifecycle and provenance rules.
- Treat taxonomy registries, schemas and governance reports as authoritative.
- Never place the correct answer in alt text, visual JSON, filenames or metadata.
- Prefer deterministic structured visual JSON over generated SVG or images.
- Do not modify main directly.
- Do not mix unrelated changes into the current task.
- Inspect existing architecture and tests before editing.
- Do not weaken validation or tests to make a change pass.
- Use strict TypeScript and existing repository conventions.
- Keep changes minimal and within the stated scope.

## Required validation

Run the relevant checks after implementation:

npm run typecheck
npm run lint
npm test
npm run validate:questions
npm run build

Run Playwright E2E tests when user-facing behaviour changes.

## Git discipline

- Check git status before editing.
- Work on the designated branch.
- Keep commits focused and intentional.
- Do not commit generated artefacts, secrets or unrelated changes.
- Report files changed, tests run, results, risks and final commit SHA.
